column5: There starting, Look at the back ground, should tell location. We went yesterday weather was great. Fishing was slow. 63FTW. Dock was not in yet at Crystal, Lots of minnows at Erie Tracker   13"  Ended the day with a couple dozen.
I've only been to one spot on Erie (not fishing) and I'm pretty sure I recognize that place.
a great start to some awesome fish fries ! its early! congrats, thanks for the early post.
Nice job Fish Farmer...that one is really fat.  Cheers  Craig
Good going. Nice meal for a foursome.
Perch are great fun. Good job guys,  MTBF

Good lookin' perch Dave!  I think I'm very familiar with that location, actually I thought it may be a little early for perch at that spot but guess I was wrong. Wife and I were going to go down this morning, got the boat all ready for the season yesterday, except for gas that is, but something came up around the house and we never got moving.  Thanks for sharing the mouthwatering pictures.

Yes Harry, was slow but a nice day to be out. Hope to be given it another shot next week. Or going after some Brown Trout at 50Pt. Looks like the guys are getting some nice Cats on the river, may give Steve's derby a go.
Nice! We got about 150 today with some fatties, report coming soon
Now that's the way to spend a day. Some very nice looking Perch in the bucket, and I know that lighthouse.... Haven't fished out of there in 20 years... Nice work!
Thinking   the same thing Dave. Maybe Sunday, gotta go to work this morning for 7.  Damn! If I'd only listened to my father I too would have been retired by now
Well this explains why you've not been over drinking my beer.
Great haul Fish Farmer I can see in your future that you'll be eating well Thanks for sharing Leechman
